companies, was charged with insider trading by the Securities and
Exchange Commission for tipping off five friends and family members
about the acquisition of Affymax by Glaxo before it was publicly
announced three years ago. Zaffaroni agreed to pay a $552,000 civil
penalty and the other five defendants will cough up $1.85 million
in ill-founded profits and penalties. By Peter Sinton
</P>
<P>
   &UR; HASBRO _ &LR;  Hasbro Inc. said it will buy Alameda-based software
maker MicroProse Inc. for about $70 million in cash, debt and
preferred stock as the No. 2 toymaker expands its computer software
production. The maker of Parker Brothers games and Tiger electronic
toys said it will pay $6 a share, or $34.5 million, for all of the
outstanding shares of MicroProse. The price also includes about
$32.5 million in assumed debt and $3 million in preferred stock. By
Benny Evangelista
</P>
