a conference table. I asked two members of this tiny club whether
they would have wanted the press and public watching their every
move. Their split decision may help you decide whether allowing the
public to eavesdrop on the antitrust case against Microsoft will
advance the cause of justice or turn the whole affair into a
carnival. By Tom Abate
