<SLUG> BC-FBN-GIANTS-NOTEBOOK-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
N.Y. GIANTS NOTEBOOK 
</HEADLINE>
  (mk) 
 By BILL PENNINGTON   
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ALBANY, N.Y. _ The New York Giants' preseason game with the
Jacksonville Jaguars on Friday night will be Tyrone Wheatley's
first chance to wrest the job of starting halfback from Tiki
Barber. Giants coach Jim Fassel said Wednesday that he planned to
use Wheatley with the team's first-string offense against
Jacksonville.
</P>
<P>
   Barber will still start the game, but Wheatley, who found little
running room behind the Giants' third-string offensive line in last
Saturday's preseason opener with Cincinnati, will get several
carries in the first half with the starting unit.
</P>
<P>
   ``I've wanted to see Tyrone run more, I've wanted to move him
up,'' Fassel said of Wheatley, who had 32 yards on 11 attempts
against Cincinnati.
</P>
<P>
   Barber, Wheatley and Gary Brown, along with fullback Charles
Way, are all vying for carries in the crowded Giants backfield.
</P>
<P>
   Wide receiver Amani Toomer made a leaping, one-handed catch at
the back of the end zone for a touchdown in a goal-line scrimmage
Wednesday. It appeared that the Giants' backup quarterback, Kent
Graham, was throwing the football away, but Toomer jumped over a
crowd of defenders to make the catch, spiking the ball after he
landed.
</P>
<P>
   ``It was unbelievable,'' Fassel said of Toomer's reception.
``That's what he can do now. Last year, he might not have been in
the right position to make that catch.''
</P>
<P>
   The Giants signed Grant Baynham, a 6-foot-5-inch, 247-pound
tight end who was waived by the Minnesota Vikings last week. With a
knee injury sidelining Al Pupunu and with the rookie tight ends
Andy Haase (flulike symptoms) and Todd Pollack (knee ligament
strain) out, Fassel was unwilling to go into Friday night's game
with one healthy tight end, Howard Cross.
</P>
<P>
   Baynham spent last year, his rookie season, on the Vikings'
practice squad. Running back Lamont Randle was waived by the Giants
to make room for him. Fassel said safety Sam Garnes, guard Ron
Stone and tackle Robert Harris would also miss Friday's game.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
