   GEEWAX-COMMENTARY _ ATLANTA _ In recent years, government
bashing has become so fashionable that many people now believe
industry can do everything better than government. Unfortunately,
about half of all states, including Georgia, have embraced the idea
that prisons can be safely run by private companies. (Geewax,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   LATHAM-COLUMN _ I remember writing these words sometime in
October of 1992: ``Do we really want to elect as president a man
who has essentially admitted being unfaithful to his wife?'' The
answer, as we must all remember, was a resounding ``Yes!'' (Latham,
Marshall News Messenger) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   BORDERS-COLUMN _ DALLAS _ The first indication that this wasn't
going to be a typical hotel stay was at the front desk of the Hyatt
Regency at Reunion Square, a hotel hard by downtown and within
walking distance of the Texas School Book Depository. The clerk
announces that the Hyatt is hosting the annual Mary Kay Inc.
conference, and that more than 1,000 are attending over the next
several days. (Borders, Nacogdoches Daily Sentinel) MOVED.
