the Big Four networks. Reruns are part of the problem, but the
other, problem is the quality of programming. Creative brain-drain
equals lackluster programs. With six networks (including weblets WB
and UPN) putting on more than 100 hours of shows, is there really
enough talent in Hollywood to support all that? (Holloway, Austin
American-Statesman). ETA: 8 p.m.
