</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-YOUNGRESTLESS-COOPER14-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    `That's Katherine Chancellor!'
 &HT;    By Loretta Grantham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. _ She is venerable, glamorous, sometimes
compassionate, always brash.
</P>
<P>
   But today, she's sick as a dog.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is, like, only the sixth time in 25 years I haven't been
able to tape the show,'' says Jeanne Cooper _ a k a Katherine
Chancellor on ``The Young and the Restless'' _ between hacking
coughs from her home in L.A. ``I keep telling myself `Not
pneumonia!' ''
</P>
<P>
   ``Mrs. Chancellor'' may have survived sailing over a cliff in a
car, the ravages of alcoholism and the rantings of arch rival, Jill
Abbott, but, Cooper deadpans: ``This sinus infection may be what
kills me in the end.''
</P>
<P>
   It's tough to separate Cooper from her character because a)
she's played Mrs. Chancellor for so long, and b) we witnessed her
get a real face-lift in 1984 _ a soap-opera first _ and worried
with her as the bandages came off.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't mind when people ask me about it because it did so
much good,'' says Cooper, who had some more facial fine-tuning (``a
rejuvenation'') last year on the show. ``It took away the fear and
the mystery.''
</P>
<P>
   Cooper, a grandmom of seven with one on the way, became Mrs. C.
in 1973.
</P>
<P>
   ``(Creator) Bill Bell wasn't pleased with the ratings, so he
added my character. I went in and read for the role, and he looked
up and said, `That's Katherine Chancellor.' ''
</P>
<P>
   And folks around the world (``Y&AMP;R'' airs in 32 countries) agree.
</P>
<P>
   Cooper says she's fond of today's more confident and outspoken
Mrs. C., who's been on the wagon for more than two decades.
</P>
<P>
   ``I can't tell you how many people have come up to me and shaken
my hand and given me a sobriety chip (a token of acknowledgment)
from Alcoholics Anonymous.''
</P>
<P>
   The youngest child of an oil-consultant dad and teacher mom,
Cooper has three kids, including actor Corbin Bernsen.
</P>
<P>
   She's also the best of pals with actress Jess Walton, who plays
Jill Abbott _ the temptress who had an affair with Phillip way back
when.
</P>
<P>
   ``We crack up all the time,'' says Cooper, who recently had to
wrestle Walton in a scene worthy of ``The Jerry Springer Show.''
``Jess didn't think our stunt doubles were being aggressive enough,
so we jumped in there and did it.''
</P>
<P>
   Interestingly, Cooper had planned to play Mrs. Chancellor for
just two years or so. But the character stuck.
</P>
<P>
   ``The key to longevity is to realize that yes, this other person
is in your life. But that no, you're not that person. Otherwise,
you'd probably blow your brains out.''
</P>
<P>
   And we know that can't happen because then Jill would win.
</P>
<P>
   Loretta Grantham is a writer for the Palm Beach Post, West Palm
Beach, Fla.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-13-98 1126EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
