<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NUDE-GROOVE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GETTING NUDE IN `GROOVE'
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By BOBB STRAUSS  
 c.1998 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   LOS ANGELES _ Another advantage of playing the mature female
partner in a movie romance: You don't have to get naked for the
love scenes.
</P>
<P>
   ``I didn't want to take all my clothes off and show it up on a
big ol' screen for all the world to see,'' says Angela Bassett,
star of the sensual romance ``How Stella Got Her Groove Back.''
``Especially not after `What's Love Got to Do With It,' and all the
attention I got based on my physicality in that movie.
</P>
<P>
   ``And that was just dancing and arms showing and shimmying, so I
can imagine ... No, I couldn't imagine. I dare not imagine ... what
would happen if I show my birthday suit up there.''
</P>
<P>
   ``We got to a point where Angela said, `I'm not comfortable
doing certain things','' says ``Groove'' director Kevin Rodney
Sullivan. ``Then I had to figure out how to communicate this idea
with no wasted motion in the two love scenes. But in general, your
imagination is more powerful than the camera can ever be. So my
approach was to get you, the viewer, to bring your own
sensibilities to bear on those scenes.''
</P>
<P>
   Well, not everything was left to the imagination. Taye Diggs,
the 26-year-old actor who plays Stella's Jamaican lover in the
movie, drops trou on camera for both of the film's steamy sex
scenes. How does he feel about being lustfully objectified?
</P>
<P>
   ``It trips me out,'' Diggs says. ``It didn't bother me at the
time we shot it, but I get a little embarrassed by it now. Luckily,
I saw it in a screening room with just me and my girl and the man
operating the projector.''
</P>
<P>
   The significant other's reaction?
</P>
<P>
   ``She loved it,'' Diggs says. ``But she sees that movie every
day.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-08-13-98 1328EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
</DOC>
