<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PLANE-CRASH INJURIES DIDN'T END JANE FROMAN'S CAREER
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: I have been trying to find this out for years: Whatever
happened to my favorite singer, Jane Froman?
</P>
<P>
   _ U.C.
</P>
<P>
   A: Froman died at age 72 on April 22, 1980, in Columbia, Mo.,
the city where she went to college and later spent her retirement
years.
</P>
<P>
   One of the most popular radio and film singers of the '30s and
'40s, Froman was seriously injured in a Feb. 22, 1943, plane crash
in Lisbon, Portugal, that killed 25 of 39 on board.
</P>
<P>
   After eight years of recovery requiring numerous surgeries,
Froman was the subject of a 1952 film ``With a Song in My Heart''
and host of ``The Jane Froman Show'' on TV for three years in the
1950s.
</P>
<P>
   Froman created a foundation that established a children's
hospital at the Menninger Clinic and retired from performing in
1962.
</P>
<P>
   Q: What's the name of the fake movie that director John Landis
works into each of his films?
</P>
<P>
   _ K.T.D., Huntsville, Ala.
</P>
<P>
   A: Landis works a throwaway reference to ``See You Next
Wednesday'' into his movies, usually on a poster or a theater
marquee.
</P>
<P>
   There is a script by that name penned by Landis as a teen-ager,
according to the ``frequently asked questions list'' of the
rec.arts.movies discussion groups on the Internet. He never plans
to film it.
</P>
<P>
   ``See You'' appears in the following films, among others: ``An
American Werewolf in London,'' ``Blues Brothers,'' ``Coming to
America,'' ``Innocent Blood,'' ``Into the Night,'' ``The Kentucky
Fried Movie,'' ``Shlock,'' ``Spies Like Us'' and ``Trading
Places.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: Did the actor Elyssa Davalos, who played Nikki Carpenter in
``MacGyver,'' also play Hillary Grant in the series ``How the West
Was Won''?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.S., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: She did _ her other credits include the movies ``Herbie Goes
Bananas,'' ``The Apple Dumpling Gang Rides Again'' and ``A House in
the Hills.''
</P>
<P>
   Davalos recently finished filming ``Between the Sheets'' with
numerous members of the DeLuise family: Dom, Carol, Peter, Michael
and David.
</P>
<P>
   Mail to her can be sent in care of SBB, 1801 Avenue of the
Stars, Suite 902, Los Angeles, CA 90067.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
</P>
