<SLUG> BC-ANIMALKINGDOM-BOX-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AND BRING YOUR WALLET
</HEADLINE>
 
(EDS: Accompanies DISNEY-ANIMAL KINGDOM) (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Animal Kingdom observes Disney park tradition by outnumbering
rides, exhibits and other attractions with ubiquitous gift shops
and restaurants. The T-shirts, backpacks, picture frames and other
insignia-festooned souvenirs are pricey but of decent quality.
</P>
<P>
   The food, sadly, also reflects Disney park history. It is
overpriced and most of it doesn't taste very good. Sandwiches at
the Flame Tree Barbecue restaurant cost almost $7, and that's
without chips. A grilled chicken salad is about six bucks, or one
dollar per shred of chicken. Drinks from vendors are at least $2.
Figure each member of your party will go through $20 just for one
meal and some snacks.
</P>
<P>
   Animal Kingdom's hours are 7 a.m.-8 p.m. daily. Adult admission
is $42 plus tax; Disney defines ``adult'' as age 10 or older.
Children ages 3-9 get in for $34. For information, call (407)
824-4321.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
