sweeping corruption investigation might send a good number of
Japan's mighty philosopher kings _ the bureaucrats who largely run
the country _ to prison. But these days, despite a Cabinet change,
nearly the only government employee who has gone anywhere is
Katsuhiko Kumazaki, the prosecutor who led a much-heralded
investigation into scandals involving expensive free entertainment
paid for by businessmen who wanted the bureaucrats' favor. By
Sheryl WuDunn.
