LEFTHAND (Undated) - Stick shifts. Can openers. Three-ring binders.
Slanted spatulas. Doorknobs. Chain saws. These are not a few of a
left-hander's favorite things. In a right-hander's world,
left-handers are left out. It may not be enough to cause
psychological problems, but frustrations mount with such simple
tasks as cutting a piece of construction paper with a set of
right-handed scissors. Which is exactly the reason for the creation
of International Lefthanders' Day. With LEFTCELEBS, LEFTFACTS,
LEFTSITES. By KATHY CANO-MURILLO and KEVIN MURPHY. &QL; 
