<SLUG> BC-LEFTHAND-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOUTHPAWS GET THE UPPER HAND 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 BY KATHY CANO-MURILLO AND KEVIN MURPHY  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - Stick shifts. Can openers. Three-ring binders. Slanted
spatulas. Doorknobs. Chain saws.
</P>
<P>
   These are not a few of a left-hander's favorite things.
</P>
<P>
   In a right-hander's world, left-handers are left out. It may not
be enough to cause psychological problems, but frustrations mount
with such simple tasks as cutting a piece of construction paper
with a set of right-handed scissors.
</P>
<P>
   Which is exactly the reason for the creation of International
Lefthanders' Day, which falls on Aug.13. Started in 1976 by
Lefthanders' International, a club for lefties, the day celebrates
society's unseen minority.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh, what a great idea!'' says lefty Stephanie Stanton, a news
reporter at Channel 3 (KTVK) in Phoenix.
</P>
<P>
   ``I remember as a child always being singled out in art class.
Our teacher would say, `Any lefties in the room? Raise your hand so
I can find you scissors.' I didn't realize it then, but later I
started noticing I was different than most people and now I know
being left-handed has a lot to do with it.''
</P>
<P>
   Stanton would rather cut off her right arm _ well, figuratively
_ than become a righty. She looks fondly at her left-handed life
and has accumulated stories to share with her grandkids someday.
Like how she thinks driving would be easier if only for a
left-handed gas pedal.
</P>
<P>
   But she has adjusted comfortably to a right-handed world, so she
really feels no need for left-handed products.
</P>
<P>
   Not all lefties feel that way.
</P>
<P>
   Gordon McGregor found right-handed products weren't handy in the
least. Today, he operates Southpaw Enterprises, a mail-order
business on the Internet that caters to the sinisters of the world
by offering dozens of left-handed gadgets.
</P>
<P>
   His aggravation goes back to his days as a telephone-wire
repairman in Canada. His biggest battle _ next to sorting colored
wires _ was using a traditional tape measure.
</P>
<P>
   He created a tape measure specially designed for southpaws, one
where the tape pulls out from the left side rather than the right.
And now telephone cables are a thing of the past.
</P>
<P>
   ``We have everything from left-handed can openers to portfolios,
but by far the tape measure is what keeps us in business
full-time,'' says Diane McGregor, Gordon's wife.
</P>
<P>
   It's safe to say being left-handed has kept Arizona Diamondbacks
pitcher Brian Anderson _ and a host of others _ in business full
time as well.
</P>
<P>
   ``There just seems to be a demand for good, left-handed
pitching,'' says Anderson, a starter. ``If you're a left-handed
pitcher and still sucking air, then you've got a chance.''
</P>
<P>
   Baseball is a sport notorious for catering to righties. Because
of the configuration of the baseball diamond, lefties must choose
from among being a pitcher, a first baseman or an outfielder.
</P>
<P>
   Although Anderson played shortstop his senior season at high
school, he's made a name for himself racking up outs on the mound
and not in the field.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's not a whole lot for lefties to play,'' says Anderson,
who also said it was difficult finding left-handed gloves as a
child in Ohio, where he grew up.
</P>
<P>
   The fraternity of southpaws is small on the Diamondbacks (six on
a 25-man roster), and like all lefties, Anderson says they all seem
to have a screw loose somewhere.
</P>
<P>
   ``We're all kind of goofy,'' Anderson says. ``Especially (first
baseman) Travis (Lee). He's got a serious goofy streak.''
</P>
<P>
   Although Anderson says he tries to be ``as right-handed as
possible,'' he is almost exclusively a southpaw.
</P>
<P>
   ``I throw left-handed, I write left-handed, I eat left-handed
and I kick left-footed,'' he says. ``But I punch right-handed,
because I don't want to injure my pitching hand.'' &QL; 
 &QL; 
To order items from Southpaw Enterprises, call 800-818-9616, or
visit http://www.southpaw.bc.ca/southpaw.html on the Internet. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
