<HEADLINE>
RIGHT ON! FACTS FIT FOR PRO-LEFTIES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - Perhaps the dictionary doesn't shine the brightest
light on lefties (check out the definition of ``sinister''). Still,
here are but a few factoids proving southpaws deserve a little more
credit than Webster's opinion alone, beginning with the ubiquitous
pro-lefty quote found on mugs and T-shirts: ``The left side of your
brain controls the right side of your body, and the right side of
your brain controls the left side of your body. So only left-handed
people are in their right mind.''
</P>
<P>
   _ZIP code 25251 is dedicated to left-handers. Left Hand, W.Va.,
does allow right-handers, but everyone there is a true Left Hander.
</P>
<P>
   _The turbot has the distinct advantage of having both eyes on
the left side of its head. The turbot is a fish, and an envied one
at that.
</P>
<P>
   _James A. Garfield was the first left-handed U.S. president. He
could, however, go both ways and would amuse visitors by
simultaneously writing in Latin with one hand and Greek with the
other. Now that's entertainment.
</P>
<P>
   _Left-handers have an advantage in baseball. A lefty batter is a
step closer to first base. A southpaw pitcher can keep an eye on
the runner at first better then a right-hander.
</P>
<P>
   _The term ``southpaw'' was started by Chicago sportswriters in
the 1890s to describe left-handed pitchers. Pitchers in the Chicago
stadium faced west toward home plate. Their pitching arms, then,
were to the south. Get it? Sportswriters are so clever.
</P>
<P>
   _Males of the left-handed persuasion outnumber females, 2 to 1.
</P>
<P>
   _Lefty Albert Einstein was called backward. As a child, speech
came slowly and he had problems in almost every subject in school.
</P>
<P>
   _Rudders on ancient sailing vessels were attached to the right
side, forcing them to dock on the left. This became the ``port''
side.
</P>
<P>
   _Thank a lefty for electricity. Ben Franklin flew a kite in 1752
and proved lightning is electricity, so if not for him, we'd be
cruising the Internet by candlelight. Or something like that.
</P>
<P>
   _The ancient Greeks were one of the few people kind to lefties.
Their word for left was ``aristera,'' meaning ``the best.'' This is
where we get the word aristocrat.
</P>
<P>
   _Tuesday is lucky for lefties. It was named for the left-handed
Scandinavian god Tiw. This is the best day to meet a southpaw.
</P>
<P>
   _The Kerr clan in Scotland believes its surname comes from the
Gaelic ``keir, `` meaning left. Many of its castles were built with
stairs winding counterclockwise, giving left-handed sword fighters
the advantage in defending against right-handed attackers.
</P>
<P>
   _Napoleon Bonaparte and Josephine are probably the most famous
left-handed couple in history. So don't anger a short lefty with a
Napoleon complex or he just might decide to take over the world. &QL; 
 &QL; 
Source: http://pw2.netcom.com/nikonman/lefties.html on the
Internet. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
