   FBC-HUSKIES (Seattle) Huskies have their first full-squad
workouts this weekend. Willie Hurst and Jelani Harrison, two
freshman running backs, will get a chance to play a lot. The team
needs help at that position.
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Chicago) Mariner pitching coach Stan Williams
laughed when recalling his first meeting with the M's pitching
staff, when he told them they could finish the season with a
composite earned run average under four runs a game. ``They must
have thought I was an alien,'' Williams said. The Mariners were the
laughingstock among major-league pitching staffs, especially the
bullpen which regularly blew leads and cost Nardi Contreras his
job. But since May 1, the staff ERA is 4.48, slightly above average
in the offensive-minded American League. The slow and meticulous
climb to respectability has reached the point where bad
performances, like Tuesday night and Wednesday afternoon in Toronto
where seventh-inning pitching collapses led to back-to-back losses,
are considered a glitch instead of a trend.
</P>
<P>
   By Jim Street. (story will move in the ``s'' category)
</P>
