<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LEIBOWITZ-COLUMN-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
BILL, MONICA AND JERRY SPRINGER 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By DAVID LEIBOWITZ  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   UNDATED - They just called over from Features with a correction
for the TV grid. You may want to tape this to the fridge, because
I'm thinking it promises to be the very latest in ``must see TV.''
</P>
<P>
   A programming note:
</P>
<P>
   Monday, Aug. 17, 2 p.m., The Jerry Springer Show: ``President
Bill Clinton testifies live before a federal grand jury.''
</P>
<P>
   That's right, kiddies, in a red-hot, unprecedented collision of
politics, pop culture and pornography, Independent Counsel Kenneth
Starr is outta here and Jerry Springer, King of the Airwaves, the
man who brought us ``hermaphrodites who cheat on themselves,'' is
in.
</P>
<P>
   Give us some Springerian hype, Jer.
</P>
<P>
   ``We've gotten wild and outrageous on the show before, folks,
but nothing like this! Today we're going to have deeper, even
darker secrets revealed! Love triangles, adultery, transactional
immunity! You probably think you've seen it all, but I'm telling
you, Bill and Monica and Hillary are really too hot for TV!''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry! Jerry! Jerry! Jerry! Let's roll that sneak preview.
</P>
<P>
   Caution: As is always the case with the U.S. Presidency in the
late 20th century, the following excerpts are not to be shown to
lifelong Democrats, children under the age of 18, or Chelsea.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Bill, you've been telling us about DNA testing and how
it was misused to frame O.J. Simpson for those two murders. That's
great, but now I want to welcome to the show another expert on DNA,
Monica the intern.''
</P>
<P>
   Bill: ``Jerry, I feel her, her pain, but she's a lyin'_''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Hey, hey! Shhh! Shut up!''
</P>
<P>
   Audience (all together, like a herd of mongoloid sheep):
``Jerry! Jerry! Jerry!''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``All right. OK. Now Monica, that is one lovely dress.''
</P>
<P>
   Monica: ``Thanks. I had it in the closet for ages. A little dry
cleaning, presto, it's good as new.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Wonderful. Now tell us, when did it all begin?''
</P>
<P>
   Bill: ``Jerry, any chance I can invoke the Fifth Amendment
here?''
</P>
<P>
   Monica (swallowing back tears): ``It was when I saw him in those
itty bitty jogging shorts. And it was wonderful, until we got
Tripped up.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``I bet. Wonderful on a dozen occasions, from what we
hear.''
</P>
<P>
   Monica: ``Then he turned into the Big Creep.''
</P>
<P>
   Bill (wagging his finger): ``Jerry, there is no improper
relationship with that woman, Miss Lewinsky.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Still, sir, you have to admit, this has been a crushing
blow for the presidency.''
</P>
<P>
   Yuck. Time to fast forward.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Now we welcome to the show Hillary, Bill's wife. Hey_''
</P>
<P>
   Hillary (running straight for Monica): ``You mouthy little
(bleep). I'll kill you! Right wing conspirator! Arkansas hater!''
</P>
<P>
   Monica: ``Bring it on, Ice Queen.''
</P>
<P>
   Hillary (reaching past the security guards for Monica's throat):
``You'll wish Newt hadn't spiked my health care proposal when I'm
done with you, freak.''
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Whoa! I'll be back in a moment with a final thought.
Stay with us.''
</P>
<P>
   Now this I've been dreaming of for months on end.
</P>
<P>
   Jerry: ``Thanks for being with us today. You know, I have to
tell you, this has been one amazing show. See, I thought that what
I do was the most sordid, vile, scum-bathed thing on the face of
the planet. Turns out, no, Washington D.C. has me beat by a
longshot. Heck, those people produce more filth in a day than I do
in a year. Except there they call it news, or politics, or justice.
It's enough to make me want to get back into politics. Or quit my
show and do something really useful for mankind, like throw myself
off the Sears Tower.
</P>
<P>
   ``Anyway, until next time, take care of yourself _ and each
other.''
</P>
<P>
   Ah, dare to dream, dare to dream. Sadly, the best we can do is
take care to change the channel, and even then it's all Bill, all
Monica, all Jerry, all the time.
</P>
<P>
   Way back when, they called the place America. Now it's Springer
Nation. &QL; 
 &QL; 
David Leibowitz can be reached at at david.leibowitz(at)pni.com &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
