<P>
   MIRANDA-RULE (Washington) _ The so-called Miranda rule requiring
the police to tell suspects of their right to remain silent has
prevented law enforcement officers from solving thousands of
violent crimes since it went into effect in 1966, a Dallas-based
think tank, the National Center for Policy Analysis, says in a new
report. By NICOLE TSONG. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   GRAMM-SECURITY (Washington) _ Sen. Phil Gramm, R-Texas, says he
will consider increased funding for security at American embassies,
despite his record of opposing more spending for diplomatic
outposts during his 1996 presidential bid. By STEVE LASH. (Already
filed)
