<P>
   US-BOMBINGS (Andrews Air Force Base, Md.) _ In a somber ceremony
that both condemned terrorism and lauded its victims, President
Clinton pays tribute to the 12 Americans killed in embassy bombings
in Africa. ``We must honor the memory of those we mourn today by
pressing the cause of freedom and justice for which they lived,''
Clinton said. By BENNETT ROTH. (Already filed)
</P>
<P>
   HARRELSON-JUDGE (San Antonio) _ The federal judge who last week
heard arguments to give convicted killer Charles Harrelson a new
trial is removing himself from the case. District Judge Fred Biery,
who held the hearing in Denver, came under fire after playing a
game of basketball with Harrelson's actor-son, Woody. By THADDEUS
HERRICK.
</P>
<P>
   COMMENTARY (``k'' category)
</P>
<P>
   MEANS-COLUMN (Hilton Head, S.C.) _ South Carolina has benefited
from the clout of two long-serving senators. Is it really ready to
abandon that power for two-term Republican Rep. Bob Inglis, a
crusader for term limits who seeks to dump five-term Democratic
Sen. Ernest F. ``Fritz'' Hollings? By MARIANNE MEANS. (Already
filed)
</P>
<P>
   SPORTS (``s'' category)
</P>
<P>
   BBN-SOSA (Chicago) _ All season long, he has been the odd man
out in the race to catch Roger Maris. While Mark McGwire and Ken
Griffey have gotten all the home-run headlines, Sammy Sosa has been
quietly plugging along in the background slugging 46 HRs and
carrying the Chicago Cubs into playoff contention for the first
time in years. By NEIL HOHLFELD.
</P>
<P>
   BBN-ASTROS (Houston) _ The Houston Astros go for their seventh
consecutive victory and try to complete a four-game sweep of the
Milwaukee Brewers at the Astrodome. By CARLTON THOMPSON.
</P>
<P>
   GLF-PGA (Redmond, Wash.) _ Full coverage of the opening round of
the PGA Golf Championship. By JAYNE CUSTRED.
</P>
<P>
   With: GLF-ROBERTSON-COLUMN
</P>
