<HEADLINE>
THE WAYS IN WHICH WE REMEMBER 
</HEADLINE>
  
 (Eds: This story also moved in the ``l'' lifestyle file)  
 By LEAH GARCHIK  
 c.1998 San Francisco Chronicle
<TEXT>
<P>
   The literary event of the week _ on tabloid TV shows, at least _
was the publication of  &UR; Christopher Andersen &LR; 's ``The Day
 &UR; Diana &LR;  Died'' (Morrow; $27), a detailed account that includes all
kinds of dark revelations. Among them:
</P>
<P>
   _ Diana's childhood nanny used to go upside her head with a
wooden spoon.
</P>
<P>
   _ Spiritual healer  &UR; Simone Simmons &LR;  detected a ``vast whirlwind
of energy'' on the left side of Diana's bed, her favorite side.
</P>
<P>
   _ According to Diana's hairdressers, there were ``at least nine
men'' in Di's life after the divorce, including  &UR; Placido &LR; 
 &UR; Domingo &LR;  and  &UR; Luciano Pavarotti  &LR; (and what's  &UR; Jose Carreras &LR; ,
chopped liver?).
</P>
<P>
   _ When the princess was having an affair with heart surgeon
 &UR; Hasnat Khan &LR; , she arranged to watch him perform surgery. She was
often nauseated by the sight, she told a friend, ``but I force
myself to watch because I want to learn as much as possible about
heart surgery.''
</P>
<P>
   _ If she could be anyone in the world, said Diana, ``I would be
 &UR; Sharon Stone &LR; .''
</P>
<P>
   _ On  &UR; Nelson Mandela &LR; 's advice, Diana contacted a Zulu shaman to
give her advice on whether she should marry  &UR; Dodi Fayed &LR; .
</P>
<P>
   _ Diana's last Christmas present from the queen was a bar of
soap.
</P>
<P>
   _ A love poem Fayed had engraved in silver and given to Diana
was actually ``borrowed'' from a poem he'd received several years
before from  &UR; Tina Sinatra &LR; , who was his girlfriend at the time.
</P>
<P>
   _ Having rushed to the Paris hospital to be at Diana's side,
 &UR; Sylvia Jay &LR; , wife of the British ambassador to France, blew her
nose into an Irish lace handkerchief as she learned of the
princess' condition.
</P>
<P>
   _ Within an hour of Diana's death, &UR; Queen Elizabeth &LR;  had aides
inquire as to whether the princess had had any of the royal jewels
with her.
</P>
<P>
   A Buckingham Palace spokesman has called the book ``complete
fantasy.''
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; LIFE AND DEATH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; _ Edwin Heaven &LR;  noticed that among the Sex Pistols featured on
one of those Levi's ``Our Models Can Beat Up Their Models''
billboards, is  &UR; Sid Vicious &LR; , who probably could have beaten up
anybody's model. In October 1978, Vicious was charged with stabbing
his girlfriend to death, and he died of a heroin overdose before he
could be tried.
</P>
<P>
   Does this make him an appropriate advertising icon? ``Icon's the
word,'' said Levi's  &UR; Brad Williams &LR; , naming some of the other
celebrities on the billboards. ``The Sex Pistols did a great many
things, but the thing they'll be remembered for is that they
invented punk rock,'' an expression of originality that ``is what
Levi's brand is all about.''
</P>
<P>
   The murder? Williams described it as just one of ``many
details'' people remember.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _ Neither  &UR; David Bowie &LR;  nor  &UR; Yoko Ono &LR;  were sponsors of ``The
 &UR; Hermann Nitsch &LR;  6-Day Orgy Mystery Theater,'' against which a
member of Congress railed recently. The Austrian artist had
disclaimed rumors of their involvement several weeks ago. The
diatribe against Bowie and Ono by Rep.  &UR; James Traficant &LR; , D-Ohio,
reported here a few days ago, did take place, but the congressman's
wrath was misdirected.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Marc Huestis &LR;  is one of many readers rejoicing in the Bay
Area Reporter's announcement that for the first time in 17 years,
the current issue of the gay and lesbian weekly contains no
obituaries for AIDS deaths. Past issues included as many as 31
obits.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   &UR; FLASH &LR;
</P>
<P>
   _ As to what  &UR; George Carlin  &LR; thought of all the brouhaha over
the Boston Globe's  &UR; Mike Barnicle &LR;  using jokes that were in
Carlin's latest book, the comedian's publicist,  &UR; Sybil Ramsey &LR; ,
read an official statement: ``Mike Barnicle is a great writer who
got burned by one of his sources. There are no hard feelings.''
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Monica Lewinsky &LR; , living as a virtual prisoner in her
mother's Washington apartment, has learned to knit and is making
chenille scarves, reports People magazine.
</P>
<P>
   _  &UR; Dan Lungren &LR; 's ``Lundgren for Governor'' Web site includes
the text of his major ``Education Policy Speech,'' in the course of
which he hopes ``that we can dedicate ourselves to reaching the
highest standards'' and mentions that  &UR; Chelsea Clinton &LR;  goes to
``Standford'' University.
