 &UR; FOR BUSINESS SECTION &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; SKUNK IPO _ &LR;  Strapped for cash and in need of repairs, Fort Bragg's
venerable Skunk Train is hoping that hitching a ride on the
Internet will help haul it out of its financial woes. THe biggest
single tourist attraction in Mendocino County is nearly sidelined
by debt and the necessity of rehabilitating its tracks, locomotives
and rolling stock. The Skunk Train, which shuttles from Fort Bragg
on Highway 1 to the town of Willits on Highway 101, is trying to
raise $4.6 million. To get it, the railroad's, 21 owners, have
decided to go public. By Ken Howe
