<HEADER>
A3140 &Cx1f; taf-z
r a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT     08-13 0098
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-QUOTE-OF-THE-DAY-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUOTATION OF THE DAY
</HEADLINE>
 (Eds.: This quotation refers to BC-AFRICA-MEMORIAL-NYT, which moved
in ``i'' news file.) 
c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``They were the kind of unpretentious but remarkable people who
represent America in diplomatic outposts around the world _ people
doing their jobs day in and day out, working for peace,
strengthening democracy, healing the ill, helping those in need,
winning friends for America.''
</P>
<P>
   _MADELEINE ALBRIGHT, the secretary of state, speaking at the
ceremony for the Americans killed in Kenya.
</P>
</TEXT>
